WikiPedia:TypeScript

Emacs has been mentioned as "providing support" for TypeScript.

As of 2016-12-23 there are packages available via melpa-stable and marmalade.

  tide               2.0.2         new        melpa-s... Typescript Interactive Development Environment
  typescript-mode    0.1           new        melpa-s... Major mode for editing typescript

  tss                0.6.0         available  melpa-s... provide a interface for auto-complete.el/flymake.el on typescript-mode.
  typescript         0.1.1         available  marmalade  Major mode for editing typescript

There are two (related?) highlight modes for TypeScript:
* [http://blogs.msdn.com/b/interoperability/archive/2012/10/01/sublime-text-vi-emacs-typescript-enabled.aspx typescript_support_for_emacs.zip] (blogs.msdn.com)
* [https://github.com/mattdeboard/dotfiles-emacs/blob/master/typescript-mode/typescript-mode.el typescript-mode.el] (mattdeboard @ github)

== IDE packages==
These provide powerful and relatively complete environments by combining and customizing other packages. 
===Spacemacs===
* [https://develop.spacemacs.org/layers/+lang/typescript/README.html TypeScript layer] for [[Spacemacs]]. It also supports TSX.
===Doom Emacs===
* [https://github.com/doomemacs/doomemacs/tree/master/modules/lang/javascript JavaScript module] for [[DoomEmacs|Doom Emacs]] includes supports for TypeScript.
==Language Server Protocol==
===LSP Clients===
* [[Eglot]]: Supports various [[https://github.com/joaotavora/eglot/blob/db91d58374627a195b731a61bead9b4f84a7e4bc/eglot.el#L231-L234 TypeScript-related modes]].
* [[LspMode]]: Supports [[https://emacs-lsp.github.io/lsp-mode/page/lsp-typescript/ TypeScript]].

== Other Extension ==

* [https://github.com/aki2o/emacs-tss tss.el] provides Intellisense-like completion, as well as syntax-checking for Typescript. Also includes a modified version of <code>typescript-mode.el</code>
* [https://github.com/ananthakumaran/tide tide] supports auto-completion via CompanyMode, syntax-validation via Flycheck, jump to definition, rename symbol, ElDoc, find occurrences and ImenuMode

